description.narrative: UNICEF significantly supported the Government to improve immunization coverages, a key result for children, by reorienting the Programme on the most deprived and hard to reach populations. In 2019, 774,247 (97 per cent) children under one year received three doses of DPT-containing vaccine and 771,542 (96 per cent) children were vaccinated against measles, exceeding the CPD target of 73 per cent. In the central and northern regions, 1,420,199 children under five were vaccinated against polio (99.7 per cent of target). A key achievement was the vaccination of nearly four million children under five against measles (83.5 per cent of target). | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
